    "), it can be stated that our template-based feedback was perceived positively, as indicated by the results in Table 9.",
    "We conducted a randomised controlled trial to find significant effects that contribute to the perception of the feedback, which was measured through six single items that were used as dependent variables.",
    "For this purpose, we conducted an ordinary least squares analysis.",
    "In our case, the treatment variable was whether or not a participant received highly informative.",
    "The provision of highly informative feedback had a positive effect on Helpfulness and a negative effect on Motivation."
